reading/writing files



- open("files.txt") returns a 'file' object
- open("files.txt", "w") allows to overwrite the 'file' object
- open("files.txt", "w") opens the file in append mode.
- readlines() returns a list fo string values from the file, one string for each line of text

EXAMPLE
for fn in os.listdir(): #returns list containing the names of the files in the current directory
	if os.path.isfile(fn): #validates 'fn' as a file
		with open(fn,"r") as f:
			entry = {}
			entry["title"] = f.readline().replace("\n","")
			f.readline()
			entry["tags"] = f.readline().replace("\n", "")
			f.readline()
			entry["body"] = f.readlines()
			dicts.append(entry)

